Greetings,<br>
<br>
Your passwords are the keys you use to access personal information that
you've stored on your computer and in your online accounts.<br>
<br>
If criminals or other malicious users steal this information, they can
use your name to open new credit card accounts, apply for a mortgage,
or pose as you in online transactions. In many cases you would not
notice these attacks until it was too late.<br>
<br>
Fortunately, it is not hard to create strong passwords and keep them
well protected.&nbsp; Intel has created the Password Checker to help you
gauge the strength of your password. Password Checker is a
non-recording feature on Intels Website that helps determine your
password's strength as you type.<br>
<br>
Visit <a href="#{url}">https://www-ssl.intel.com/content/www/us/en/forms/passwordwin.html</a>
to test the strength of your passwords.<br>
<br>
